descriptions.en: Broader or bigger unit (e.g., Cluster, Plots, Admin Unit) of a survey, if the survey contains more than one unit level.
Form-like structure, important for an entity that needed to enter data once for the particular unit
Specific entity information in a tabular format, "tree" as an example; entity selection will depend on the objective.
1st level unit no, this could be Cluster number, Plot Number, Administrative Unit, etc.
A second-level unit is measured under the broader first-level unit (depends on survey design). There could be several second-level units.
This could be a plot, a sub-plot, a household, etc, which is a smaller unit and measured under the first-level unit.
If this unit or location has a local name, it could be more related to socio-economic surveys

labels.en: Any Major disturbances in the area?

descriptions.en: Like storms, cyclones, earthquakes, droughts, etc. Detailed information could be collected on frequent events as well, using a tabular entity (see Tree example)
